The Council for Traditional and Alternative Medicines has barred the use of Hensha medicine, popularly known as ‘mkongo’, over irregularities. The traditional medicine is being manufactured and distributed by Nyasosi Traditional Clinic and canceled the drug registration. Council for Traditional and Alternative Medicines chairperson, Prof Hamisi Malebo announced the decision in Morogoro regional Wednesday, claiming Mkongo with the Council’s registration number TZ17TM0027, was found to be mixed with a modern male enhancement drug called sildenafil ( Viagra). “The Act is against the law and the guidelines of the registration of natural and alternative medicine,” Prof Hamisi Malebo told reporters. He said the center has been ordered to remove the drug from the market immediately. "Failure to do so, strict legal measures will be taken against the owner," he added.